11:T724,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How is local SEO different from regular SEO?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Regular SEO chases rankings on standard search results. Local SEO is built for the map pack: Google Business Profile, citations, reviews, and location pages. If your customers search by city or \"near me,\" you need both, but local is what puts you on the map."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does local SEO cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Single-location businesses start at $1,500 per month. Multi-location brands scale from $3,000 to $5,000+ based on how many markets you cover and how tight the competition is. We quote after looking at your locations and current visibility."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many Google reviews do I need?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There is no magic number. In competitive markets, staying in the top three map spots often means 50 to 100+ reviews. We focus on steady monthly volume and thoughtful responses, not a one-time push that fades."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need Local SEO or full SEO?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Start with Local SEO ($1,500/mo entry) if map pack visibility and Google Business Profile are your main gaps. Choose full SEO ($2,500/mo entry) if you need technical site work, content, and link building for broader organic growth. Many local service businesses run both. We recommend the mix on a strategy call."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you manage multiple Google Business Profiles?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. We run multi-location accounts with separate content, review workflows, and reporting per market. Franchises and multi-branch operators are a big part of what we do."}}]}6:[[["$","script","0",{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"h